JONATHAN ALFERNESS:
Product management,

00:00:41.930 --> 00:00:45.030
and I lead up our mobile
display ads teams.

00:00:45.030 --> 00:00:47.500
We thought that we would
spend some time today

00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:50.030
talking with all of
you about what we're

00:00:50.030 --> 00:00:54.520
seeing in the mobile app space
in terms of monetization;

00:00:54.520 --> 00:00:59.550
how people are building not
just small businesses, but truly

00:00:59.550 --> 00:01:03.709
global businesses on the backs
of mobile apps; the trends

00:01:03.709 --> 00:01:05.750
that we're seeing, the
techniques that people are

00:01:05.750 --> 00:01:08.650
using, and importantly,
some of the tools

00:01:08.650 --> 00:01:11.090
that we're building to make
this easier for all of you.

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.440
We're going to look at this
in three specific areas--

00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:22.420
first, this concept of
smarter monetization.

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:25.120
How you can take advantage
of data and tools

00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:27.860
that exist today, both
manual and automatic,

00:01:27.860 --> 00:01:30.670
to build really
innovative business models

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:32.980
on the backs of mobile apps.

00:01:32.980 --> 00:01:37.620
Second, the tools that you
need to scale your businesses.

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:40.480
Many app developers
start with a couple

00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:43.210
of folks in their garage,
and before they know it,

00:01:43.210 --> 00:01:45.950
they've created a
multimillion dollar business.

00:01:45.950 --> 00:01:48.760
You want to make sure that
the tools that you adopt

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:50.290
into your app are
tools that will

00:01:50.290 --> 00:01:53.050
help you to scale
from small businesses

00:01:53.050 --> 00:01:54.870
to multi-billion dollar ones.

00:01:54.870 --> 00:01:57.160
And three, simplicity.

00:01:57.160 --> 00:02:01.470
Because most importantly,
you guys are app developers.

00:02:01.470 --> 00:02:04.410
You want to spend your time
thinking about the apps

00:02:04.410 --> 00:02:07.280
that you're building, making
those better, creating really

00:02:07.280 --> 00:02:10.560
rich, engaging experiences--
and the last thing

00:02:10.560 --> 00:02:13.310
that you want to worry about
is letting monetization,

00:02:13.310 --> 00:02:15.230
or business models,
get in the way.

00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:20.630
Now, I've had an
incredible opportunity

00:02:20.630 --> 00:02:24.550
working with AdMob, my
team, and my partners

00:02:24.550 --> 00:02:27.110
for the better part of the
last three or four years.

00:02:27.110 --> 00:02:31.410
And without a doubt, one of
the best experiences that I get

00:02:31.410 --> 00:02:34.050
is to travel this
wonderful globe

00:02:34.050 --> 00:02:37.920
and to meet app developers
in all regions of the world.

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.700
I get to meet app
developers right here

00:02:39.700 --> 00:02:42.010
in my hometown of
San Francisco, I

00:02:42.010 --> 00:02:44.300
get to meet amazing
developers in places

00:02:44.300 --> 00:02:48.000
like Japan and Tokyo
and London, as well

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:50.670
as in places like Vietnam.

00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:53.630
And it's stunning, because
these stories are the same over

00:02:53.630 --> 00:02:58.050
and over again-- you find
bright, young entrepreneurial

00:02:58.050 --> 00:03:00.320
folks who know that
they can change

00:03:00.320 --> 00:03:03.560
the world with some software
on a mobile application.

00:03:03.560 --> 00:03:06.140
And we understand
that the barriers

00:03:06.140 --> 00:03:08.070
of the world, these
country borders

00:03:08.070 --> 00:03:11.870
are fading away, as people in
the furthest reaches of Earth

00:03:11.870 --> 00:03:14.210
are building businesses
that are touching us

00:03:14.210 --> 00:03:16.316
all around the world.

00:03:16.316 --> 00:03:18.440
So we thought we would
start with just two examples

00:03:18.440 --> 00:03:22.070
to give you a feel for how
folks are turning mobile apps

00:03:22.070 --> 00:03:25.510
into truly global businesses.

00:03:25.510 --> 00:03:28.490
The first is a story
of our friend Mehmet.

00:03:28.490 --> 00:03:32.240
He's the co-founder
and CEO of Gram Games.

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:35.030
Mehmet grew up in Turkey
in a small village

00:03:35.030 --> 00:03:37.530
called [? Golnar. ?] He
dropped out of college,

00:03:37.530 --> 00:03:40.230
but he always had a
passion for engineering,

00:03:40.230 --> 00:03:42.410
for software development,
and for coding.

00:03:42.410 --> 00:03:46.100
And so he taught
himself to program.

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:47.670
Mehmet was a little
bit ambitious,

00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:49.360
and within three
weeks he was trying

00:03:49.360 --> 00:03:53.140
to figure out how to
write AI for chess games.

00:03:53.140 --> 00:03:55.180
He worked for a variety
of different companies

00:03:55.180 --> 00:03:59.520
as a developer, but he had this
itch for his passion, which

00:03:59.520 --> 00:04:00.550
was gaming.

00:04:00.550 --> 00:04:06.660
And so he co-founded a
company, Gram Games, in 2012.

00:04:06.660 --> 00:04:08.280
Wasn't easy at first.

00:04:08.280 --> 00:04:10.640
You can see how they
operated when they first

00:04:10.640 --> 00:04:13.370
got started-- about
five of them working out

00:04:13.370 --> 00:04:16.089
of their apartments, as
you kind of have to do.

00:04:16.089 --> 00:04:20.850
And they were working really
hard to try to develop a hit.

00:04:20.850 --> 00:04:23.020
They kept building app
after app after app,

00:04:23.020 --> 00:04:24.820
but nothing was sticking.

00:04:24.820 --> 00:04:27.980
And then all of a
sudden, in 2014,

00:04:27.980 --> 00:04:29.650
the winds changed for them.

00:04:29.650 --> 00:04:33.469
And they developed
a truly massive hit.

00:04:33.469 --> 00:04:35.260
I hope some of you of
you in the audience--

00:04:35.260 --> 00:04:37.712
raise your hand, come on,
who's played 10 10 Puzzle?

00:04:37.712 --> 00:04:38.420
I certainly have.

00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:40.190
Yeah, see, there we go.

00:04:40.190 --> 00:04:42.300
And you see how quickly
the stuff spreads.

00:04:42.300 --> 00:04:46.280
Before long, they had 5 million
users playing this game.

00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:48.380
And they realized, now
we have an opportunity

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:50.600
to build a business.

00:04:50.600 --> 00:04:53.670
So they employed
in-app purchases,

00:04:53.670 --> 00:04:57.010
trying to get users to pay
to play more of the game

00:04:57.010 --> 00:04:58.790
that they loved.

00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:01.960
But with 5 million users, and
with not a high percentage

00:05:01.960 --> 00:05:03.610
of users willing
to pay, they really

00:05:03.610 --> 00:05:07.030
struggled to create a business
off of in-app purchase.

00:05:07.030 --> 00:05:13.120
Late in 2014, they started
researching mobile app

00:05:13.120 --> 00:05:17.030
advertising systems, and
they came upon AdMob.

00:05:17.030 --> 00:05:18.960
Mehmet liked AdMob
because it had a high fill

00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:21.580
rate, strong CPMs,
which meant it

00:05:21.580 --> 00:05:26.490
was going to deliver him revenue
without a lot of complexity.

00:05:26.490 --> 00:05:30.400
So in the back half of 2014,
they implemented AdMob.

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:34.120
And before they knew it, they
were generating $5,000 a day

00:05:34.120 --> 00:05:37.355
in earnings-- which grew
their business seven-fold.

00:05:41.461 --> 00:05:44.910
They utilized mobile ads
in a fairly simple way,

00:05:44.910 --> 00:05:48.160
leveraging banner
ads for in-game play,

00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:50.035
and then interstitials
in between the levels.

00:05:53.360 --> 00:05:56.230
And thanks to AdMob,
they were able to move

00:05:56.230 --> 00:05:58.760
from their apartment
to new offices.

00:05:58.760 --> 00:06:01.294
They grew from five
employees to 20,

00:06:01.294 --> 00:06:02.710
and they've now
scaled-- they have

00:06:02.710 --> 00:06:06.789
20 million users worldwide.

00:06:06.789 --> 00:06:09.330
And see an example up there,
you can see their team behind me

00:06:09.330 --> 00:06:10.829
here, you can see
their new offices.

00:06:10.829 --> 00:06:12.530
And they're one of
the fastest growing

00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:14.910
startups in all of Turkey.

00:06:14.910 --> 00:06:16.450
And the thing that
really impresses

00:06:16.450 --> 00:06:20.090
me is that they have such
a passion about this space,

00:06:20.090 --> 00:06:22.380
that they now run
their own accelerator

00:06:22.380 --> 00:06:28.610
program to help other indie game
developers get off the ground.

00:06:28.610 --> 00:06:32.590
Our next example comes
from Backflip Studios.

00:06:32.590 --> 00:06:34.920
Julian is the co-founder
and CEO there,

00:06:34.920 --> 00:06:38.580
and they have one of the oldest
and most favorite of mobile app

00:06:38.580 --> 00:06:39.612
games.

