00:09:48.040 --> 00:09:50.730
are taking advantage
of Google solutions

00:09:50.730 --> 00:09:53.650
to help them grow
their businesses.

00:09:53.650 --> 00:09:56.270
Our solutions, and the
solutions that we're building,

00:09:56.270 --> 00:10:00.730
we hope to empower all of you
to grow app businesses just

00:10:00.730 --> 00:10:05.840
as quickly, just a
scaled around the world.

00:10:05.840 --> 00:10:07.570
We talk about
scale-- I think it's

00:10:07.570 --> 00:10:10.630
absolutely important to
understand that yes, we're

00:10:10.630 --> 00:10:11.370
Google.

00:10:11.370 --> 00:10:13.840
And yes, this is a
Google I/O conference.

00:10:13.840 --> 00:10:16.970
But we're here to
serve app developers,

00:10:16.970 --> 00:10:20.280
regardless of the platform
that they choose to operate on.

00:10:20.280 --> 00:10:22.640
AdMob has been committed
to cross platform

00:10:22.640 --> 00:10:26.860
on both iOS and Android long
before Google purchased AdMob.

00:10:26.860 --> 00:10:30.900
This was the case, and it
continues through to today.

00:10:30.900 --> 00:10:34.230
Over the last 12 months,
we have seen equal growth

00:10:34.230 --> 00:10:37.180
on the iOS and Android
platforms in terms

00:10:37.180 --> 00:10:41.870
of the number of developers
that are adopting our products.

00:10:41.870 --> 00:10:44.070
And if you want to
hear about scale,

00:10:44.070 --> 00:10:47.561
we've grown to a very
significant scale

00:10:47.561 --> 00:10:49.310
in terms of the number
of apps that we now

00:10:49.310 --> 00:10:53.820
serve-- over 650,000-- and
in terms of the ad requests

00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:55.220
that we see every month.

00:10:55.220 --> 00:11:01.115
That number is now 200
billion ad requests a month.

00:11:01.115 --> 00:11:02.740
And you think a little
bit about this--

00:11:02.740 --> 00:11:05.420
we are seeing the
growth of the mobile ads

00:11:05.420 --> 00:11:10.800
ecosystem, the mobile ads in-app
ecosystem at Google directly.

00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:12.670
But that is growth
that we expect,

00:11:12.670 --> 00:11:14.530
and folks outside
of Google expect,

00:11:14.530 --> 00:11:18.420
to continue for the
foreseeable future at least.

00:11:18.420 --> 00:11:21.540
In fact, the predictions
suggest that mobile, in-app ads

00:11:21.540 --> 00:11:26.680
are set to grow three-fold in
roughly the next three years.

00:11:26.680 --> 00:11:29.420
And important to understand--
because I know many folks

00:11:29.420 --> 00:11:31.690
think that mobile
ads in apps make up

00:11:31.690 --> 00:11:33.540
a small slice of
the revenue, most

00:11:33.540 --> 00:11:36.530
coming from in-app purchase--
that is no longer the case.

00:11:36.530 --> 00:11:37.860
And you'll see why in a second.

00:11:37.860 --> 00:11:40.090
But in many of
the major markets,

00:11:40.090 --> 00:11:45.265
mobile ads now represent 50% or
more of the total app revenue

00:11:45.265 --> 00:11:46.765
that our app
developers are earning.

00:11:49.520 --> 00:11:51.520
So I think the question
is, what's driving this?

00:11:51.520 --> 00:11:56.014
What's driving this continued
increase in mobile ads?

00:11:56.014 --> 00:11:58.180
And if we look at it, we
believe that there's really

00:11:58.180 --> 00:12:00.040
three distinct trends.

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:03.500
First, as always, is users.

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:07.420
And users vote with their
clicks, as they're doing here.

00:12:07.420 --> 00:12:11.756
90% of all apps that are
downloaded today are free.

00:12:11.756 --> 00:12:13.630
And you can see the
phenomenal growth-- there

00:12:13.630 --> 00:12:15.170
it is-- you can see the
phenomenal growth that we've

00:12:15.170 --> 00:12:16.669
had in app downloads
over the years,

00:12:16.669 --> 00:12:19.100
and projections moving forward.

00:12:19.100 --> 00:12:23.100
But also recognize that that
little, darker bar at the top,

00:12:23.100 --> 00:12:24.820
that's it for the paid apps.

00:12:24.820 --> 00:12:28.200
More and more users know that
they can download and engage

00:12:28.200 --> 00:12:33.200
and play truly
phenomenal apps for free,

00:12:33.200 --> 00:12:34.866
and they're voting
with their finger.

00:12:34.866 --> 00:12:35.990
So that's trend number one.

00:12:35.990 --> 00:12:38.590
Trend number two, in-app
purchase works, it

00:12:38.590 --> 00:12:41.720
works great for those that
know how to really optimize

00:12:41.720 --> 00:12:43.990
and tune it, it's
absolutely phenomenal.

00:12:43.990 --> 00:12:46.900
But dammit, you better do
a good job of turning it,

00:12:46.900 --> 00:12:55.982
because only 1.5% of users, of
mobile gamers, spend in apps.

00:12:55.982 --> 00:12:57.690
So you've got to find
that right audience

00:12:57.690 --> 00:13:00.210
if in-app purchase is the only
way you're going to monetize.

00:13:00.210 --> 00:13:03.790
And even more complicated,
in-app purchase tendencies

00:13:03.790 --> 00:13:04.970
vary a lot per region.

00:13:07.887 --> 00:13:09.970
So while that business
model might do well for you

00:13:09.970 --> 00:13:11.950
in Korea or Japan,
for example, you

00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:15.340
might struggle as users
don't end up paying

00:13:15.340 --> 00:13:19.130
as much in the US or the UK.

00:13:19.130 --> 00:13:20.800
The third trend
that we really think

00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:24.580
is transforming mobile ads
is much, much better user

00:13:24.580 --> 00:13:25.850
experiences.

00:13:25.850 --> 00:13:28.010
We highlight three here.

00:13:28.010 --> 00:13:30.480
The first is native advertising.

00:13:30.480 --> 00:13:33.670
So because we're bringing ads
into these experiences that

00:13:33.670 --> 00:13:36.270
feel like the experiences
that users are in,

00:13:36.270 --> 00:13:39.060
it's much less
jarring, and I think

00:13:39.060 --> 00:13:40.702
the word native is perfect.

00:13:40.702 --> 00:13:41.910
This is the way folks see it.

00:13:41.910 --> 00:13:45.610
They see it as native to the
environment that they're in.

00:13:45.610 --> 00:13:47.354
The second is that
we're starting

00:13:47.354 --> 00:13:49.520
to see the transformation
that we've been expecting,

00:13:49.520 --> 00:13:52.120
with rich media
ads, full screen,

00:13:52.120 --> 00:13:55.100
interstitial-- we call them
light box ads at Google--

00:13:55.100 --> 00:13:56.940
the uptake here has
been very significant.

00:13:56.940 --> 00:14:00.640
These are much easier to
create than in years past.

00:14:00.640 --> 00:14:02.830
They provide rich interaction.

00:14:02.830 --> 00:14:05.500
They allow users to actually
interact with the products

00:14:05.500 --> 00:14:07.960
that they're
considering purchasing.

00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:09.530
And the last has
been video-- video

00:14:09.530 --> 00:14:13.170
has transformed mobile overall,
and the advertising space

00:14:13.170 --> 00:14:15.130
is no exception.

00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:17.950
So publishers are able
to earn a lot more money

00:14:17.950 --> 00:14:19.340
with these types of formats.

00:14:19.340 --> 00:14:22.320
And with Google, you can
leverage TrueView ads,

00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:24.740
which put the user in control.

00:14:24.740 --> 00:14:27.660
So the user has the choice
to skip the ad if it's not

00:14:27.660 --> 00:14:31.440
relevant to her desires.

00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:34.300
Ultimately, all of
this momentum is

00:14:34.300 --> 00:14:37.420
leading to a very, very
significant market.

00:14:37.420 --> 00:14:43.290
Most projections estimate the
mobile app advertising market

00:14:43.290 --> 00:14:44.540
to be north of $50 billion.

00:14:44.540 --> 00:14:51.030
This suggests $60
billion by 2017.

00:14:51.030 --> 00:14:53.000
$60 billion is an
awful lot of money,

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.250
and it's one of the
things in at least

00:14:55.250 --> 00:14:58.230
my experiences that is pushing
more and more folks to want

00:14:58.230 --> 00:15:00.330
to become app developers.

00:15:00.330 --> 00:15:05.980
You want your own opportunity
to get a slice of this pie.

00:15:05.980 --> 00:15:08.930
But you're going to
have to think carefully,

00:15:08.930 --> 00:15:11.570
because the competition
is increasing,

00:15:11.570 --> 00:15:13.690
and the business models
are getting more complex.

00:15:13.690 --> 00:15:15.680
And if you just choose
simple business models,

00:15:15.680 --> 00:15:18.070
like in-app purchase
or advertising,

00:15:18.070 --> 00:15:20.400
chances are you're
going to come up short,

00:15:20.400 --> 00:15:22.170
and you're not going
to be able to compete

00:15:22.170 --> 00:15:25.730
against some of the other
folks who are out there.

00:15:25.730 --> 00:15:27.570
And we believe that
until now, developers

00:15:27.570 --> 00:15:32.940
have not had the right
tools to really embrace

00:15:32.940 --> 00:15:36.370
the opportunity that's out there
to create these new business

00:15:36.370 --> 00:15:37.050
models.

00:15:37.050 --> 00:15:40.010
And that's what we've
been so hard at work

00:15:40.010 --> 00:15:44.500
at Google at an AdMob building
for the last 18 months or so.

00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:47.010
Solving monetization
on apps is a passion

00:15:47.010 --> 00:15:49.300
that doesn't just
consume me, but consumes

00:15:49.300 --> 00:15:51.022
my team on a daily basis.

00:15:51.022 --> 00:15:53.480
That's why we're so excited
about some of the announcements

00:15:53.480 --> 00:15:56.300
we have today.

00:15:56.300 --> 00:15:59.160
So what should the
strategy be for your app?

00:15:59.160 --> 00:16:02.060
How can you do it better?

00:16:02.060 --> 00:16:04.580
And why is it important
to get it right now?

00:16:07.270 --> 00:16:09.960
Well, the competition is
growing, as I mentioned.

00:16:09.960 --> 00:16:13.990
In 2014 alone, one
million new apps

00:16:13.990 --> 00:16:15.990
were created and
uploaded to the stores.

00:16:18.510 --> 00:16:22.100
There's almost six million
developers now, worldwide,

00:16:22.100 --> 00:16:25.530
with one and a half million
developers in North America

00:16:25.530 --> 00:16:27.950
alone.

00:16:27.950 --> 00:16:29.980
And this number will also grow.

00:16:29.980 --> 00:16:33.810
As the democratization of
software development, coding

00:16:33.810 --> 00:16:36.090
and distribution continues
to blanket the world,

00:16:36.090 --> 00:16:41.020
we expect eight million
developers by the year 2017.

00:16:41.020 --> 00:16:43.534
All of this means more
competition for all of you

00:16:43.534 --> 00:16:45.700
as app developers-- for the
eyeballs, the mindshare,

00:16:45.700 --> 00:16:49.514
and ultimately the
monetization of your users.

00:16:49.514 --> 00:16:51.930
So we're here to give you some
tips, some thoughts that we

00:16:51.930 --> 00:16:54.600
have about what's going
to help all of you

00:16:54.600 --> 00:16:56.590
break out from the rest
of the competition.

00:16:56.590 --> 00:16:58.700
Here's three.

00:16:58.700 --> 00:17:01.290
First, we believe
you need to realize

00:17:01.290 --> 00:17:04.720
the full value of each user.

00:17:04.720 --> 00:17:09.130
Not all users will interact
with in-app purchases.

00:17:09.130 --> 00:17:12.180
Not all are going to
interact with ads.

00:17:12.180 --> 00:17:14.010
And that's what we're
demonstrating here.

00:17:14.010 --> 00:17:16.151
We have a set of users
who are likely to spend

00:17:16.151 --> 00:17:18.109
in in-app purchase, but
a separate set of users

00:17:18.109 --> 00:17:19.920
who are likely to click on ads.

00:17:19.920 --> 00:17:21.940
And a third set who
maybe aren't going

00:17:21.940 --> 00:17:23.970
to engage with
either one of those,

00:17:23.970 --> 00:17:27.220
but who will happily
spread the good word of how

00:17:27.220 --> 00:17:29.370
well your app works,
or how awesome

00:17:29.370 --> 00:17:31.930
your game is on social media.

00:17:31.930 --> 00:17:34.410
You should probably-- and
the sophisticated developers

00:17:34.410 --> 00:17:36.750
in the audience are nodding,
because you get it--

00:17:36.750 --> 00:17:39.480
you should probably be dealing
with these users differently,

00:17:39.480 --> 00:17:42.450
and be building hybridized
business models that

00:17:42.450 --> 00:17:43.750
take all of them into account.

00:17:46.410 --> 00:17:48.920
The second tip we'd
have-- and I've

00:17:48.920 --> 00:17:51.070
been talking about this
for the last three years,

00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:56.870
easily-- please, use a mobile
apps analytics package.

00:17:56.870 --> 00:17:58.360
Google Analytics
works great, we're

00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:01.710
going to talk more
about that in a second.

00:18:01.710 --> 00:18:04.190
The Google Analytics team
has been really working

00:18:04.190 --> 00:18:06.720
hard to build the best mobile
apps analytics package,

00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:08.040
we'd love for you to use them.

00:18:08.040 --> 00:18:10.880
But for you guys, and for
your own businesses' sake,

00:18:10.880 --> 00:18:13.510
make sure you use some
analytics package.

00:18:13.510 --> 00:18:15.370
Because even though
we've been out espousing

00:18:15.370 --> 00:18:16.860
how important this
is, and when you

00:18:16.860 --> 00:18:19.880
do you get the nods from
everybody you talk to,

00:18:19.880 --> 00:18:22.825
look at this stat.

00:18:22.825 --> 00:18:24.200
I'm sorry for the
language, but I

00:18:24.200 --> 00:18:26.760
don't know what the hell the
other 79% of the app developers

00:18:26.760 --> 00:18:28.970
are doing-- you're
not able to understand

00:18:28.970 --> 00:18:31.780
what the hell's going
on inside your app.

00:18:31.780 --> 00:18:36.200
But it's not sufficient
just to use analytics.

00:18:36.200 --> 00:18:39.000
Mike Shipper, my good friend
who helps me with these slides,

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:40.500
he and I created
this visualization.

00:18:40.500 --> 00:18:43.150
We love it because
we're of the age

00:18:43.150 --> 00:18:45.960
that we grew up with Hobbit
and Lord of the Rings

00:18:45.960 --> 00:18:48.950
and all that long
before the movies.

00:18:48.950 --> 00:18:51.800
And if you remember
The Hobbit, you

00:18:51.800 --> 00:18:54.610
remember Bilbo Baggins
and the cast of characters

00:18:54.610 --> 00:18:58.250
climbing to the mountain,
to the Lonely Mountain,

00:18:58.250 --> 00:19:00.630
because the dragon
Smaug had come in,

00:19:00.630 --> 00:19:04.020
knocked out all the dwarves,
and sat perched on top

00:19:04.020 --> 00:19:06.600
of the dwarves' treasure hold.

00:19:06.600 --> 00:19:09.000
Mike and I thought this
was almost comical.

00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:12.070
Like, what the hell
is a dragon going

00:19:12.070 --> 00:19:15.070
to do with all of this gold?

00:19:15.070 --> 00:19:16.680
It's the same thing
with the data.

00:19:16.680 --> 00:19:19.160
You can't just have a
data analytics package

00:19:19.160 --> 00:19:20.270
and let it sit there.

00:19:20.270 --> 00:19:24.010
You are sitting on a veritable
treasure trove of information,

00:19:24.010 --> 00:19:26.335
and we implore you to
take action on the data

00:19:26.335 --> 00:19:27.460
that you've been acquiring.

00:19:30.160 --> 00:19:34.610
The third suggestion we
have is to truly maximize

00:19:34.610 --> 00:19:36.230
your ad yield.

00:19:36.230 --> 00:19:40.590
You have so many opportunities
for monetization, so many

00:19:40.590 --> 00:19:43.450
different avenues that you
can bring ads and different ad

00:19:43.450 --> 00:19:45.400
formats in, make
sure you're looking

00:19:45.400 --> 00:19:48.990
as holistically as possible,
use a yield management solution

00:19:48.990 --> 00:19:51.960
if you have one, and make
sure that every impression is

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:54.540
maximized to the most possible.

00:19:54.540 --> 00:19:58.090
What you see here-- we
just cut off the y-axis

00:19:58.090 --> 00:20:00.550
so we wouldn't share
the actual CPM values--

00:20:00.550 --> 00:20:03.550
but these are relative
CPMs on our network

00:20:03.550 --> 00:20:06.762
of TrueView versus
interstitials versus banners.

00:20:06.762 --> 00:20:08.470
So you might say, OK,
well I'm just going

00:20:08.470 --> 00:20:10.437
to use TrueView all the time.

00:20:10.437 --> 00:20:12.270
But that may not work
for all of your users,

00:20:12.270 --> 00:20:15.300
and you may not get 100%
fill rate on TrueView.

00:20:15.300 --> 00:20:18.090
So think about the other ad
formats that you can mix in,

00:20:18.090 --> 00:20:18.920
as well.

00:20:18.920 --> 00:20:21.190
Because ultimately,
different formats

00:20:21.190 --> 00:20:23.710
will bring a richer
experience to your app,

00:20:23.710 --> 00:20:24.770
and help you earn more.

00:20:27.460 --> 00:20:29.560
Talking about interstitials,
specifically, we've

00:20:29.560 --> 00:20:34.080
been out evangelizing how
great interstitials are--

00:20:34.080 --> 00:20:36.740
from an advertiser perspective,
absolutely; from a publisher

00:20:36.740 --> 00:20:39.130
perspective, because
you can earn more money;

00:20:39.130 --> 00:20:41.850
and from a user perspective,
because believe it or not,

00:20:41.850 --> 00:20:44.360
interstitials end up being
a little less disruptive.

00:20:44.360 --> 00:20:47.740
Most app developers are able
to swap out about five banner

00:20:47.740 --> 00:20:50.540
ads for a single interstitial.

00:20:50.540 --> 00:20:52.490
And you're able to
more carefully place

00:20:52.490 --> 00:20:55.770
those into the flow of the game,
simulating the kinds of things

00:20:55.770 --> 00:20:58.170
that users are used to,
like TV commercials.

00:20:58.170 --> 00:21:00.800
And when our app developers
make use of interstitials,

00:21:00.800 --> 00:21:02.370
they don't use it all the time.

00:21:02.370 --> 00:21:04.960
But those who do use some
interstitials see on average

00:21:04.960 --> 00:21:08.510
20% more revenue than those
app developers who don't.

00:21:11.430 --> 00:21:14.530
Speaking of demand, speaking
of different formats,

00:21:14.530 --> 00:21:16.350
when you're thinking
about the networks

00:21:16.350 --> 00:21:18.659
that your plugging into
your monetization tool--

00:21:18.659 --> 00:21:20.700
this is something known
as mediation, typically--

00:21:20.700 --> 00:21:23.910
but you can always plug
multiple third party ad networks

00:21:23.910 --> 00:21:28.750
into just about any monetization
tool for apps, including AdMob.

00:21:28.750 --> 00:21:32.990
These networks all
perform differently.

00:21:32.990 --> 00:21:35.535
Mediation doesn't solve all
these problems automatically

00:21:35.535 --> 00:21:37.660
for you-- we're going to
talk about the innovations

00:21:37.660 --> 00:21:39.610
that we're bringing--
you need to keep

00:21:39.610 --> 00:21:42.110
an eye on how these various
networks are performing.

00:21:42.110 --> 00:21:45.610
Because Network A might do
better on Wednesdays in China,

00:21:45.610 --> 00:21:48.396
but Network B might do
better on Tuesdays in the US.

00:21:48.396 --> 00:21:50.770
And you want to make sure that
you're optimizing these ad

00:21:50.770 --> 00:21:53.129
networks correctly, so
that you're maximizing

00:21:53.129 --> 00:21:54.420
your yield on every impression.

00:21:57.410 --> 00:21:59.320
So now I want to
go a little deeper.

00:21:59.320 --> 00:22:01.470
I want to talk about
what we're working on

00:22:01.470 --> 00:22:03.510
at AdMob, the
features and the tools

00:22:03.510 --> 00:22:06.450
that we have built to
help you take advantage

00:22:06.450 --> 00:22:10.150
of some of these tips and tricks
that we just talked about.

00:22:10.150 --> 00:22:12.154
So as we said in the
beginning, the principles

00:22:12.154 --> 00:22:14.070
that we're leveraging
here, and the principles

00:22:14.070 --> 00:22:16.180
that we're focused
on, are the same

00:22:16.180 --> 00:22:17.820
that we're driving into AdMob.

00:22:17.820 --> 00:22:20.890
First is to build a
platform they truly

00:22:20.890 --> 00:22:23.550
enables smart monetization.

00:22:23.550 --> 00:22:27.150
Where AdMob itself is a bit
of an optimization engine,

00:22:27.150 --> 00:22:29.830
with data and users
fed in and us trying

00:22:29.830 --> 00:22:32.220
figure out the right
monetization opportunity

00:22:32.220 --> 00:22:34.440
for the right user
at the right time.

00:22:34.440 --> 00:22:39.700
Second, make sure that you're
employing tools to scale.

00:22:39.700 --> 00:22:41.680
So what are we doing at
Google to really help

00:22:41.680 --> 00:22:44.480
you scale your business
from a demand perspective?

00:22:44.480 --> 00:22:46.875
And last, how can we make
this as easy as possible?

00:22:50.850 --> 00:22:54.780
So as I said, AdMob, the
focus and the real theme

00:22:54.780 --> 00:22:56.260
of AdMob for the
last three years

00:22:56.260 --> 00:22:59.521
now has been an
audience-aware smart platform.

00:23:02.110 --> 00:23:03.770
The simplest way
to think about this

00:23:03.770 --> 00:23:05.990
is that AdMob can
take a set of inputs--

00:23:05.990 --> 00:23:08.700
in this case it's monetization
opportunities-- it also

00:23:08.700 --> 00:23:11.220
takes as a set of
inputs all of the data

00:23:11.220 --> 00:23:13.810
that it's seen about all
of the users you have

00:23:13.810 --> 00:23:17.050
and their behavior in-app.

00:23:17.050 --> 00:23:18.640
And churning
through this engine,

00:23:18.640 --> 00:23:20.800
we can either put the
power in your hands,

00:23:20.800 --> 00:23:22.600
or we can do it
automatically, and we

00:23:22.600 --> 00:23:25.190
can provide that right
monetization opportunity

00:23:25.190 --> 00:23:26.700
to the right user
at the right time.

00:23:26.700 --> 00:23:29.197
In this case, AdMob decided
a video ad would probably

00:23:29.197 --> 00:23:29.780
monetize best.

00:23:32.510 --> 00:23:34.980
Let's look at another example,
where we take advantage

00:23:34.980 --> 00:23:38.199
of the IAP business model.

00:23:38.199 --> 00:23:40.740
So we have this feature in AdMob
called In-app purchase house

00:23:40.740 --> 00:23:41.239
ads.

00:23:41.239 --> 00:23:45.220
And the idea here is, these
will help you promote your IAP

00:23:45.220 --> 00:23:49.080
items to those users who are
actually going to purchase.

00:23:49.080 --> 00:23:51.260
And generally, when
I talk to developers,

00:23:51.260 --> 00:23:54.110
these users are precious.

00:23:54.110 --> 00:23:56.400
And what I hear is,
whatever you do,

00:23:56.400 --> 00:23:58.730
make sure that you
build the best ring

00:23:58.730 --> 00:24:00.370
fence you can around
my purchasers--

00:24:00.370 --> 00:24:03.269
don't ever show them an ad,
only show them in-app purchases.

00:24:03.269 --> 00:24:05.560
Sure, for everybody else,
you can do whatever you want,

00:24:05.560 --> 00:24:08.420
but please don't muck
with these purchasers.

00:24:08.420 --> 00:24:12.430
So this is what AdMob does
automatically on your behalf.

00:24:12.430 --> 00:24:17.360
We're able to figure
out who the buyers are.

00:24:17.360 --> 00:24:19.300
You heard [? Sumnder ?]
on stage--

00:24:19.300 --> 00:24:22.930
we have incredible computer
scientists, massive sets

00:24:22.930 --> 00:24:26.440
of machines, of computers,
and some of the best machine

00:24:26.440 --> 00:24:28.630
learning systems in the world.

00:24:28.630 --> 00:24:32.980
We're employing these to help
us predict those users that we

00:24:32.980 --> 00:24:37.060
believe are likely to be
purchasers, both aggregately

00:24:37.060 --> 00:24:38.830
and inside your app.

00:24:38.830 --> 00:24:40.350
And we can wall
those off for you,

00:24:40.350 --> 00:24:42.550
and we can make sure that
those users that we think

00:24:42.550 --> 00:24:44.910
are bound to purchase
in your app only see

00:24:44.910 --> 00:24:47.240
your IAP promotions.

00:24:47.240 --> 00:24:50.000
And for everybody else,
we're happy to help

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:51.210
you show them ads.

00:24:51.210 --> 00:24:52.810
The right ads at
the right time that

00:24:52.810 --> 00:24:57.080
are going to monetize
best for those users.

00:24:57.080 --> 00:24:58.930
This is one of these
hybrid business models

00:24:58.930 --> 00:25:00.060
that we've talked about.

00:25:00.060 --> 00:25:02.560
You're no longer just doing
IAP, you're no longer just doing

00:25:02.560 --> 00:25:05.094
ads, but now you're doing a
hybrid of the two of them.

00:25:05.094 --> 00:25:06.510
And when we started
running trials

00:25:06.510 --> 00:25:08.630
with some of our partners
earlier this year,

00:25:08.630 --> 00:25:11.109
the results that we saw
were quite stunning.

00:25:11.109 --> 00:25:13.400
This is an example that's
going to walk you through one

00:25:13.400 --> 00:25:14.590
of those sets of results.

00:25:14.590 --> 00:25:17.720
This is with LunaSoft, who
is a developer down in Korea.

00:25:17.720 --> 00:25:19.560
Now, these numbers
aren't the exact numbers,

00:25:19.560 --> 00:25:21.580
but they were benchmarked
against those numbers

00:25:21.580 --> 00:25:24.290
to represent the
uplift that we saw.

00:25:24.290 --> 00:25:28.200
In the initial experiment,
they ran for six days,

00:25:28.200 --> 00:25:31.700
and they just used their
traditional IAP business model.

00:25:31.700 --> 00:25:37.800
They showed 145,000 impressions
to all of their users.

00:25:37.800 --> 00:25:39.830
But remember, only a
small slice of those users

00:25:39.830 --> 00:25:42.637
will actually engage
with these purchases.

00:25:42.637 --> 00:25:45.220
So what that means is that your
monetization rate in aggregate

